                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/6957: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Lagos</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jester</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-12-04T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 4, 1940—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Dakar reports French belief that British are planning a thrust against the Ivory
                    Coast from their Gold Coast headquarters at Kumasi to railway at Bouaké. Please
                    telegraph such information as you may be able to obtain discreetly as to size of
                    British forces which might be available for such an attempt.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
